      <item>
        <title>Install Atom Editor on Ubuntu</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Installing or updating Atom editor on Ubuntu or Linux Mint is not possible
through apt-get but is quite easy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, download the package using &lt;code&gt;wget&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;wget https://atom.io/download/deb
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the download is finished, install the package using &lt;code&gt;dpkg&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo dpkg --install atom-amd64.deb
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally launch atom editor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;atom
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and you have it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.dilek.me/assets/Screenshot-2015-05-29.png&quot; alt=&quot;Atom screenshot&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
